                {
                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3nk36r3p/manifest/annotation/p2",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>left his wife &amp; children to want &amp; he (<lb/>\n                <persName>Mr Holstein</persName>) went in partnership with<lb/> this butcher &amp;\n                did not send to his business<lb/> at all for which he came for. He did not<lb/>\n                teach the children would not butcher as a (Schoet)<lb/> ought to have done) for an\n                Israelite; also on a<lb/>\n                <date>Sabbath</date> he smoked, butchered became beastly<lb/> drunk, &amp; tried\n                more than once to drive the<lb/> poor woman (whom he had ruined already by<lb/>\n                depriving the mother of a husband &amp; the<lb/> children of a father) in the street\n                &amp; insulting<lb/> her in every manner possible that he made himself<lb/> so\n                obnoxious that the children of this town<lb/> both Jews &amp; Christians stare at\n                him when they<lb/> saw him <persName>Mrs Stein</persName> the forsaken woman\n                with<lb/> her children moved in a house which was<lb/> bought by her husband &amp;\n                    <persName>Mr Holstein</persName> bought<lb/> the house from her husband so that\n                he<lb/> could drive the poor suffering soul out into<lb/> the street but he did not\n                succeed as well as he<lb/> expected for by breaking the peace so often &amp;c<lb/>\n                the law was on her side &amp; at last he was<lb/> arrested with <persName>Mr\n                    Stein</persName> &amp; placed in jail where<lb/> thanks be to the Almighty he\n                will stay there<lb/> but in my opinion he ought to rot there his<lb/> lifetime.\n                Being advised by the leading<lb/> Israelites to write the above facts so that\n                the<lb/> whole world should know it &amp; so take caution<lb/> Hoping that you will\n                correct all mistakes</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3nk36r3p/canvas/p2"
                }
              ]
